Yes he was successful

I am not sure. He developed feelings for another man at boarding school but his friend passed away from tuberculosis

Yes he was very heartbroken.  He never got to confess his love for him.

Nobody else knew. But he named his machine Christopher, after his friend.
Do you think Christopher was the reason why he was able to decrypt the machine?
He had an epiphany, and realized he can program the machine to decode words he already knows exist in certain messages.
What did the messages convey?
I am not sure what the messages said.
Do you think it was a good message?
No, they were probably not.
Did someone want to get the machine back from him?
A Soviet spy tried to trick him into telling about his machine
